Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.40,0:00:04.73,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.90,0:00:07.04,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are so many tangerines.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.04,0:00:09.48,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Take as many as you'd like today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.90,0:00:13.32,Naoya,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Terauchi Naoya (30) \NTetsuji's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.99,0:00:12.81,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You're our only customers today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.81,0:00:14.49,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}There's no need for restraint.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.06,0:00:27.54,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.87,0:00:28.84,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.03,0:00:30.00,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.84,0:00:35.09,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}If you harvest them so carelessly, \Nyou'll damage the tangerines.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.88,0:00:34.34,Tetsuji,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,473)}Terauchi Tetsuji (62) \NTerauchi Tangerine \NFields Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.51,0:00:36.92,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,We're sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.92,0:00:38.23,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,This is how you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.34,0:00:43.57,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.57,0:00:44.35,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.70,0:00:47.86,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, you don't have to say it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.34,0:00:50.61,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,These tangerines are my precious children.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.06,0:00:54.15,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let anyone treat them so carelessly!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.60,0:00:58.84,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,That attitude is the reason people \Nstopped coming to pick tangerines.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.27,0:01:05.04,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So this is what he meant when he \Nsaid we were his only visitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.04,0:01:11.31,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.31,0:01:14.67,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,My father can get nasty when \Nit comes to tangerines.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.10,0:01:16.79,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Don't let it bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.13,0:01:18.39,Nobuko,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Terauchi Nobuko (58) \NTetsuji's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.79,0:01:18.55,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He's just an awkward man.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.07,0:01:19.84,DCMain,SONOK,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.84,0:01:20.99,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.99,0:01:23.22,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm heading back down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.48,0:01:26.35,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,When you get there, could you send it up?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.62,0:01:28.16,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.16,0:01:30.51,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Pick lots of fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.51,0:01:32.98,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll cook up something tasty for you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.31,0:01:34.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.96,0:01:42.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.45,0:01:43.76,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.76,0:01:48.42,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I just haven't seen my mom in \Nsuch a good mood in a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.42,0:01:49.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.28,0:01:53.02,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Lately she's been arguing with my dad a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.02,0:01:54.05,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,She's been on edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.47,0:01:56.97,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't tell them that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.49,0:01:58.70,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.16,0:02:16.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Time is the y-axis, and I'm the x-axis!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.43,0:02:18.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Inscribing love and cases \Nwith deductive reasoning!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.49,0:02:21.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The aroma of citrus fruit drifts through \Ntangerine fields in perfect picnic weather!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.21,0:02:23.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.84,0:02:25.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.70,0:02:28.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.97,0:04:14.98,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(404,1)}The Sun Sets Over Tangerine Fields
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.05,0:04:12.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Sun Sets Over Tangerine Fields!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.23,0:04:23.97,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,We ended up picking a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.97,0:04:25.91,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,There's got to be a month's worth here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.28,0:04:28.98,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's stop harvesting and head back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.73,0:04:34.54,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Do we have to hike down the \Nmountain carrying these?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.29,0:04:37.54,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.89,0:04:39.96,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,We've got a convenient tool for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.44,0:04:42.80,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's coming right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.28,0:04:52.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.68,0:04:56.85,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,An agricultural monorail \Nfor transporting crops.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.52,0:05:00.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no one riding it. Is that okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.45,0:05:04.99,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It automatically goes up and down \Nthe mountain when you activate the lever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.36,0:05:06.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Automatically?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.17,0:05:09.58,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Once it reaches the work shed at the peak,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.58,0:05:13.06,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,it automatically switches into \Nreverse and returns to the shed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.51,0:05:15.75,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,at the foot of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.99,0:05:17.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.95,0:05:20.75,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, it can be \Noperated manually as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.75,0:05:22.25,ForwardReverse,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse     Forward
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.25,0:05:24.54,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's really convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.54,0:05:28.84,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to this thing, transporting \Ncrops has become much easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.17,0:05:31.90,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's load the containers onto the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.90,0:05:33.35,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.95,0:05:42.07,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,We're finally finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.07,0:05:43.53,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.94,0:05:45.86,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Kid, want to ride the monorail?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.86,0:05:46.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.96,0:05:48.95,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since you have the opportunity, why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.30,0:05:50.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.48,0:05:54.24,DCMain,SONOK,0000,0000,0000,,I want to ride, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.43,0:05:56.91,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, it's overloaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.19,0:05:59.42,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.06,0:06:01.79,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,See you at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.80,0:06:08.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa. It shakes a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.70,0:06:12.60,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on tight so you don't fall off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.82,0:06:28.32,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,These look delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.56,0:06:31.11,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen a bunch of these dishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.59,0:06:33.51,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Try some.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.51,0:06:35.33,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.44,0:06:39.83,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.83,0:06:41.29,DCMain,SONOK,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.29,0:06:43.66,DCMain,SONOK,0000,0000,0000,,Tangerines go with everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.09,0:06:46.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.12,0:06:48.63,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.63,0:06:51.34,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,My tangerines are the best in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.59,0:06:54.44,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I think you must be right. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.44,0:06:55.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.55,0:06:57.24,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.24,0:07:00.77,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, have some \Nof more of this and that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.62,0:07:04.27,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He's acting really different.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.63,0:07:07.40,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,He's happy because you \Ncomplimented his tangerines.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.40,0:07:08.53,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,He's a simple man, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.34,0:07:13.91,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you'd better not be saying \Nthings you shouldn't again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.23,0:07:16.79,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I was just complimenting you, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.74,0:07:20.23,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be shy. Eat as much as you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.23,0:07:21.69,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.22,0:07:28.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Whew. I'm stuffed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.12,0:07:30.92,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.96,0:07:35.22,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,You found a buyer for the farm?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.52,0:07:36.31,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.31,0:07:39.67,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you consult me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.67,0:07:42.68,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. It's someone we can trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.68,0:07:44.48,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.87,0:07:48.40,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I was making my own arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.40,0:07:51.24,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell Nobuko about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.81,0:07:52.74,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.25,0:07:54.36,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.86,0:07:57.70,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Because she always takes your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.70,0:08:00.12,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,She'd obviously be against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.12,0:08:04.37,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Then all the more reason for \Nus to discuss this as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.37,0:08:05.63,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the head of this family.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.56,0:08:09.41,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,I have the right to decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.01,0:08:20.67,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's when we first started \Nthe tangerine farm together.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.67,0:08:25.02,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's the first time Naoya \Nharvested a tangerine by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.44,0:08:27.02,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,How cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.02,0:08:31.53,Tangerine,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Terauchi Tangerine Farm
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.53,0:08:31.53,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,This is when Naoya told me he'd \Nwork on the tangerine farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.04,0:08:34.28,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised you remember all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.79,0:08:38.16,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's like your family's \Nhistory. It's truly wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.46,0:08:41.65,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Things were really great back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.61,0:08:50.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.42,0:08:55.51,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,A lot happens to a family over a few decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.51,0:09:00.99,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Want to see more?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.99,0:09:01.87,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.49,0:09:03.27,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.24,0:09:06.97,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.82,0:09:09.19,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.58,0:09:12.61,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's nothing serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.10,0:09:16.25,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's a frozen shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.25,0:09:17.70,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.07,0:09:21.11,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine. You can't overcome age.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.11,0:09:22.96,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.96,0:09:25.99,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Get the third one from the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.71,0:09:28.51,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.51,0:09:30.00,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.06,0:09:32.46,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.79,0:09:35.79,DCMain,TETSUJI,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Pretty handsome, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.79,0:09:37.12,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.12,0:09:38.97,DCMain,SONOK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.62,0:09:44.98,DCMain,SONOK,0000,0000,0000,,How pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.60,0:09:47.98,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe this view.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.40,0:09:50.98,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad Nobuko-san told us to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.33,0:09:52.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.34,0:10:00.05,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.05,0:10:00.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.83,0:10:05.00,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,This sound...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.35,0:10:08.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Someone must've come to pick us up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.30,0:10:13.31,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.31,0:10:14.88,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.40,0:10:21.01,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He noticed us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.60,0:10:30.42,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,He just fell, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.42,0:10:31.44,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.02,0:10:41.20,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.57,0:10:45.12,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I was watching from below, and \Nit looked like my dad fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.56,0:10:46.50,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.35,0:10:48.37,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.36,0:10:53.74,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.91,0:10:56.00,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.57,0:11:12.23,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The deceased is Terauchi Tetsuji-san, \Nthe manager of this tangerine farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.64,0:11:15.85,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The cause of death was a skull fracture.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.85,0:11:20.41,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, he hit his head \Non a rock when he fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.63,0:11:27.40,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And you saw Tetsuji-san fall?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.40,0:11:28.25,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.67,0:11:33.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, how did \Nyou notice Tetsuji-san fell?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.03,0:11:39.55,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I was making repairs near \Nthe sprinkler control panel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.78,0:11:41.25,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Where is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.65,0:11:45.28,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,It's near the base of the \Nmountain southeast of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.70,0:11:46.73,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.22,0:11:51.54,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I turned to look when I heard the girls' shouts,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.92,0:11:56.57,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,and just happened to witness my \Nfather falling from the monorail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.35,0:11:58.69,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.88,0:12:03.18,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I was looking for ingredients for dinner \Nin the fields at the base of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.61,0:12:07.58,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Like Naoya, I heard the girls' shouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.75,0:12:11.42,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.42,0:12:16.92,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be natural to think \NTetsuji-san lost his balance
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.92,0:12:22.25,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,when he let go of the monorail to \Nwave to Ran-san and her friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.75,0:12:28.18,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But why was Tetsuji-san \Nheading towards the peak?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.43,0:12:31.03,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I asked him to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.03,0:12:32.46,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.46,0:12:36.44,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I told Ran-san and her friends \Nto go watch the sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.44,0:12:40.28,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Since it'd be dark by the time they \Nreturned, I asked him to go get them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.36,0:12:43.45,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.71,0:12:48.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it seems like there's \Nblood on the inside of his hat,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.68,0:12:51.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but there's nothing on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.27,0:12:53.01,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.01,0:12:54.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think that's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.09,0:12:59.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Tetsuji-san died when he hit \Nhis head on a rock, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.89,0:13:05.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then normally wouldn't the rock have \Nleft a mark on the outside of the hat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.76,0:13:07.80,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.80,0:13:13.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Tetsuji-san lost his hat \Nbefore he hit his head on the rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.72,0:13:14.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.67,0:13:18.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then when did the blood get \Non the inside of the hat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.72,0:13:21.39,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.39,0:13:26.88,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,We saw the moment he fell. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.46,0:13:28.49,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.27,0:13:33.87,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So where is the monorail \Nyour husband was riding?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.27,0:13:36.37,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,It should be at the shed at \Nthe foot of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.56,0:13:38.21,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.21,0:13:42.21,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's have the others hold things \Ndown here while we go check that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.21,0:13:42.88,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.57,0:14:01.15,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where did they go?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.85,0:14:06.13,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Mom. It's okay, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.13,0:14:07.28,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.28,0:14:08.95,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,You've got me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.64,0:14:27.30,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing unusual about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.49,0:14:29.15,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.98,0:14:36.81,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The number of containers doesn't add up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.40,0:14:43.51,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't these containers...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.53,0:14:47.50,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing particularly \Nsuspicious about the incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.50,0:14:50.65,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,so it's safe to assume it was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.65,0:14:51.82,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.39,0:14:56.20,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's our fault for calling \Nout to him and waving.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.36,0:14:57.42,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.42,0:15:01.79,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,He shouldn't have let go of the \Nrailing while riding the monorail.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.31,0:15:05.30,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,It's my dad's fault for \Nnot following the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.73,0:15:07.10,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.10,0:15:10.39,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,He should've sounded the monorail's horn.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.84,0:15:12.80,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's because he waved with his right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.36,0:15:17.97,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. I've figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.48,0:15:23.40,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's safe to assume this incident \Nwas an unfortunate accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.40,0:15:25.72,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We should get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.87,0:15:32.24,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.04,0:15:40.37,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're always such a tedious \Nman, Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.64,0:15:42.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.04,0:15:43.88,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko, could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.05,0:15:46.88,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,There's something that \NI just don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.37,0:15:48.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What don't you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.98,0:15:54.55,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, do you remember what Tetsuji-san did
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.55,0:15:56.01,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,when we waved to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.31,0:15:57.50,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What he did?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.98,0:16:03.27,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I think he raised his hand high \Ninto the air and waved back at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.46,0:16:07.31,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. Tetsuji-san had a frozen shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.31,0:16:10.48,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Someone like that couldn't \Nraise their hand high up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.05,0:16:12.40,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.69,0:16:14.00,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.00,0:16:17.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true that your husband \Nhad a frozen shoulder?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.33,0:16:20.16,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.40,0:16:26.59,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Tetsuji-san was probably \Nforced to wave his hand
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.59,0:16:29.55,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,by someone behind him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.93,0:16:34.93,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But only Tetsuji-san was riding the monorail.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.19,0:16:39.56,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,That person was probably hiding \Nin the bed of the monorail.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.75,0:16:41.25,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.25,0:16:44.81,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There's no space for anyone to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.18,0:16:46.98,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Not now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.02,0:16:49.72,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.72,0:16:54.32,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi, there are footprints on \Nthe front of the monorail bed, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.55,0:16:56.32,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.69,0:17:00.37,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by the footprints, \Nthey belonged to Tetsuji-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.37,0:17:04.46,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Could you place your feet in \Nthem and try sitting on the bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.60,0:17:07.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Here? Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.03,0:17:09.18,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.18,0:17:13.84,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,How was he able to sit with \Nhis feet in this position?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.29,0:17:15.31,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.31,0:17:19.35,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps there was an additional \Nrow of containers there
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.78,0:17:22.72,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,so the culprit could hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.06,0:17:24.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.34,0:17:30.40,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, I don't think an adult \Ncould hide inside these containers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.68,0:17:31.90,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.85,0:17:38.66,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.15,0:17:44.66,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko-kun, do you still insist the \Nculprit hid inside a container?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.96,0:17:48.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, look at what I found.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.61,0:17:52.00,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It seems to be a folded container.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.40,0:17:54.17,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.85,0:17:59.93,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The bottoms and sides of those \Ncontainers can be adjusted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.32,0:18:04.72,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,If you fold the bottoms, three \Ncontainers can be merged into one,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.72,0:18:08.41,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,creating a space large enough \Nfor a person to hide inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.93,0:18:14.95,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, if you leave the right \Nside that we couldn't see open,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.51,0:18:20.95,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,it's even possible to make Tetsuji-san wave \Nfrom inside the container without anyone noticing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.12,0:18:23.45,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.69,0:18:27.96,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Several similar containers were \Nscattered around the tangerine fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.37,0:18:29.76,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.76,0:18:33.80,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,the culprit hid inside the folded \Ncontainers and pushed Tetsuji-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.80,0:18:38.34,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,then used the monorail's \Nautomatic return system
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.49,0:18:42.85,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,to pass before us and return \Nto the foot of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.99,0:18:45.56,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Later, they exited the monorail,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.56,0:18:50.06,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and pretended they saw Tetsuji-san \Nfall when they ran to the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.91,0:18:52.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.77,0:18:54.98,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So, who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.57,0:18:56.57,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.14,0:18:59.98,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Naoya, you—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.98,0:19:04.40,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I killed my father, put him on that monorail,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.40,0:19:06.11,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,and pushed him so it would \Nlook like an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.11,0:19:07.58,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.78,0:19:09.58,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell us more at—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.77,0:19:12.96,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! I'm the one who killed my husband!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.33,0:19:14.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.10,0:19:15.46,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.46,0:19:19.72,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I hid the hammer I used to strike \Nmy husband under the workbench.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.72,0:19:24.73,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,If you examine the fingerprints on the \Nhammer, it should prove that I'm the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.53,0:19:28.73,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.28,0:19:30.47,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.47,0:19:32.60,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I could ask you the same question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.60,0:19:35.97,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you try to take the fall for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.97,0:19:38.74,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.74,0:19:40.82,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's not your fault at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.82,0:19:44.24,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who decided to kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.77,0:19:48.24,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What happened between you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.72,0:19:53.20,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I overheard them talking \Nabout selling the farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.20,0:19:55.40,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought he was doing it to repay the debt
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.40,0:19:59.04,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,he accrued fooling around \Nwith other women.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.04,0:20:01.54,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.54,0:20:05.04,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who suggested he sell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.04,0:20:06.01,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.40,0:20:10.73,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,We wouldn't survive operating \Nthis farm as a single family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.73,0:20:13.80,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I recommended selling the farm
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.80,0:20:17.77,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,so it could be revitalized \Nusing new techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.08,0:20:19.46,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Not realizing that,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.46,0:20:23.18,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I was desperate to leave this farm to Naoya,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.99,0:20:25.28,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,so I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.61,0:20:29.96,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd properly discussed \Nselling the farm as a family,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.96,0:20:31.29,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,then this wouldn't have happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.70,0:20:34.11,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,My father told me not to say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.11,0:20:36.92,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,He said my mother would never allow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.31,0:20:39.54,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.91,0:20:44.08,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,When I told my mother about the plan to \Nsell the farm on the way to the shed,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.08,0:20:46.30,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,she suddenly started crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.53,0:20:51.31,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,When I asked her about it, she confessed \Nthat she'd killed my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.90,0:20:54.60,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,If only it'd been written off as an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.06,0:20:58.31,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,But if my mom was a suspect...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.89,0:21:02.79,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I know it was a misunderstanding, \Nbut she killed my father to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.79,0:21:06.32,DCMain,NAOYA,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I decided to take the fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.87,0:21:11.39,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have told you \Nno matter what you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.73,0:21:13.91,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.47,0:21:19.10,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for using you as witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.13,0:21:21.34,DCMain,NOBUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.09,0:22:45.80,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,These are so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.04,0:22:50.02,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,They taste better since \Nwe picked them ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.52,0:22:51.25,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.30,0:22:57.37,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. Naoya-san said \Nhe'd protect the tangerines.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.37,0:22:58.76,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.67,0:23:00.66,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.66,0:23:03.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you shouldn't eat so many at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.59,0:23:04.66,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.66,0:23:08.44,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Tangerines are low in calories so I won't \Nget fat no matter how many I eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.73,0:23:10.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you heard the expression,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.50,0:23:13.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Fruit is gold in the morning, \Nsilver at noon, and lead at night?"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.97,0:23:15.88,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.88,0:23:20.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Your liver turns excess sugar into fat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.53,0:23:24.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they say not \Ntoo eat too much fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.48,0:23:27.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,People tend not to exercise at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.76,0:23:32.55,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you should've mentioned \Nsomething that important sooner!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.55,0:23:37.43,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,My stomach feels squishier than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.43,0:23:38.43,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.40,0:23:42.59,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It won't turn into fat that quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.19,0:23:47.88,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You want to use the APTX4869 antidote
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.88,0:23:50.88,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,to restore your body so you \Ncan participate, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.88,0:23:52.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you'd understand, Haibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.73,0:23:53.66,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.15,0:23:54.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.25,0:23:56.58,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.78,0:24:01.09,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,BIG might've won if \NHigo-san were in the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.28,0:24:03.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Chiyari City?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.99,0:24:05.96,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Heartfelt Strap \N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.44,0:24:14.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is \N"The Heartfelt Strap, Part One!"
